Germany Won’t Raise Bailout Fund Volume, Finance Ministry Says

-- B y   P a t r i c k   D o n a h u e
-- 
2011-09-30T09:50:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/germany-won-t-raise-bailout-fund-volume-finance-ministry-says.html
Germany  won’t increase its
contribution to the euro-area bailout package after the lower
house of parliament approved the enhancements to the European
Financial Stability Facility yesterday, the  Finance Ministry 
said today.   “That’s it -- finito,” Foreign Ministry spokesman Martin
Kotthaus told reporters today in Berlin.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Patrick Donahue at 
 pdonahue1@bloomberg.net  